# No Ad-hoc Typography, Sizing, or Aspect Utilities

Do not hardcode typography, sizing, or aspect values in templates.

- Avoid classes like `text-[...]`, `text-xs/sm/lg`, `font-*`, `leading-*`, `tracking-*` for body/headline styling.
- Avoid arbitrary sizing classes like `min-h-[...]`, `w-[...]`, `max-w-[...]`, `h-[...]`, `gap-[...]`, and similar bracket-value utilities.
- Never use raw arbitrary aspect values like `aspect-[21/9]` in templates.
- Use approved design-system components and tokenized classes only.
- If a required style does not exist yet, add/extend it in the design system first and use a named utility/class.
- For hero media, use a named utility (example: `aspect-hero`) backed by design-system tokens/config, not `aspect-[21/9]`.

## Must Prevent

- Should never happen: multiple arbitrary Tailwind values not backed by token classes.
- Should never happen: arbitrary sizing classes such as `min-h-[26rem]`, `md:min-h-[22rem]`, `w-[4.5rem]`, `max-w-[11rem]`.
- Should never happen: arbitrary typography values.
- Should never happen: raw arbitrary aspect value usage (for example `aspect-[21/9]`).

## Examples

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<div class="text-[0.8125rem] font-medium leading-snug">...</div>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<BaseOverline>...</BaseOverline>
```

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<p class="text-sm leading-6">...</p>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<p class="text-body-sm">...</p>
```

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<img class="aspect-[21/9] w-full object-cover" />

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<img class="aspect-hero w-full object-cover" />
```
